Primary Functional Feeding Group: collector-gatherer (CG), collector-filterer (CF), predator (PR), scraper (SC), shredder (SH), macrophyte herbivore (MH), omnivore (OM), parasite (PA), piercer-herbivore (PH), xylophage (XY). Multiple entries are allowed and are separated with a comma
Habit: burrowers (BU), climbers (CB), clingers (CN), sprawlers (SP), swimmers (SW), skaters (SK). Multiple entries are allowed and are separated with a comma
Number of broods or generations of an organism in a year (also referred to as 'voltinism'): univoltine (UNI), semivoltine (SEMI), or multivoltine (MULTI).
Thermal preference assignments: cold stenotherm (stenoc), cold (cold), cool (cool), cowa (cool/warm), warm (warm), warm stenotherm (warm), eurythermal
Taxonomic Serial Number - a unique, persistent, non-intelligent identifier for a scientific name in the context of the Integrated Taxonomic Information System (ITIS).
